# Vortica Project Context

## Overview
Vortica is a marketing website built with Next.js 15 and React 19. It uses TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Radix UI primitives, Framer Motion, and utility-first styling.

## Key Features
- Multi-page marketing site with home, about, services, contact, work, and thank-you pages
- Dynamic service detail page under `app/services/[slug]/page.tsx`
- Reusable UI components and sections for consistent layout and styling
- Analytics integration and utility helpers in `src/lib`

## Project Structure
- `app/`
  - `page.tsx` — homepage
  - `about/page.tsx`
  - `contact/page.tsx`
  - `services/page.tsx`
  - `services/[slug]/page.tsx` — service detail pages
  - `thank-you/page.tsx`
  - `work/page.tsx`
  - `globals.css` — global styling
  - `layout.tsx` — root layout for metadata and wrappers
  - `analytics.ts` — analytics initialization
- `components/`
  - `Footer.tsx`
  - `Header/` — header animations
  - `layout/Navbar.tsx`
  - `sections/` — page sections like Hero, Services, Trust, WorkPreview, CTA
  - `ui/` — buttons, inputs, labels, page shell, animated controls, service cards, and a sheet component
- `content/`
  - `home.ts`
  - `services.ts`
  - `site-copy.ts`
- `lib/`
  - `analytics.ts`
  - `utils.ts`
- `docs/` — design or project scope notes
- `public/` — static assets

## Tooling and Dependencies
- `next` for server-rendered React pages
- `react` / `react-dom`
- `typescript`
- `tailwindcss`, `postcss`, `autoprefixer`
- `eslint`, `eslint-config-next`
- `@radix-ui/react-dialog`, `@radix-ui/react-label`, `@radix-ui/react-slot`
- `framer-motion`, `lucide-react`, `react-intersection-observer`

## Useful Commands
- `npm run dev` — start development server
- `npm run build` — production build
- `npm run start` — start production server
- `npm run lint` — run linter

## Notes
This repository appears to be a polished front-end marketing site with a service-focused structure and animated, component-driven UI.
